  Popeye (Robin Williams in his first movie role) rows into the harbor of Sweethaven looking for his long lost Pappy (Ray Walston) and is immediately hailed as a stranger and an outcast by the inhabitants of the sleepy little seaside villiage. He meets a hamburger addicted man named Wimpy (Pauly Dooley) and a skinny woman named Olive Oyle (Shelly Devuall) who is the fiancee to town bully Bluto (Paul L. Smith). She falls for Popeye&#039;s charm and they adopt a baby boy named SweetPea. Bluto wants to take his revenge on the town since Olive dumped him. Taxes in Sweethaven have been imposed on everything by the unseen Commodore, using Bluto as his enforcer. Popeye comes to the rescue.
